        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-27T16:31:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-27T16:31:00-05:00" n="244"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                <head>244. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Station in Guatemala</gloss> to <gloss
                        type="to">Operation <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>
                        Headquarters in Florida</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d244fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 11, Folder 5. Secret; Operational Immediate; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>. Repeated to the Director of
                        Central Intelligence.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Guatemala City</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1954-06-27T21:31:00+00:00">June 27, 1954, 2131Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>981. 1. <gloss target="#t_JMBLUG1">JMBLUG</gloss> enroute at this moment 1245
                    hours local time for conference with <gloss target="#t_STANDEL1">STANDEL</gloss>
                    1 and general staff following telephone call from <gloss target="#t_STANDEL1"
                        >STANDEL</gloss> 1 and SUMAC who have intimated they wish to turn govt over
                    to Junta. Obvious govt situation desperate despite communiqué to effect that
                    govt will fight house by house until end.</p>
                <p>2. Since army has shown no guts in past do not believe they can be expected to
                    show courage now.</p>
                <p>3. Believe govt on point of surrendering.</p>
                <p>4. Have briefed <gloss target="#t_JMBLUG1">JMBLUG</gloss> that govt must agree to
                    following points act or deny statements issued by <persName corresp="#p_CJH1"
                        >Calligeris</persName>: <list>
                        <label>A.</label>
                        <item>Arrest Communist and other leaders responsible for situation.</item>
                        <label>B.</label>
                        <item>Declaration martial law.</item>
                        <label>C.</label>
                        <item>Cessation of hostilities.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
